\"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"South Africa won its third silver - and sixth overall - medal at theParis Olympics 2024on Saturday.\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 496, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 397, \"end\": 409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.496930476628876e-12, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Enjoy the Paris Olympic Games 2024 experience at your favourite ATKV Resort!\", \"from\": 498, \"to\": 574, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 562, \"end\": 566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ATKV\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"ATKV\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ATKV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ATKV\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jo-Ane van Dykfinished second in the women's javelin with a throw of 63.93.\", \"from\": 576, \"to\": 651, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Japan'sHaruka Kitaguchitook gold with a season's best throw of 65.80, while the Czech Republic'sNikola Ogrodnikovafinished third with 63.68.\", \"from\": 653, \"to\": 793, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 653, \"end\": 658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9940286540238926, \"rank\": 0.0052234538512412314, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Van Dyk wonR200 000for her silver medal, as promised by the South African Sports Confederation and Olympic Committee (Sascoc) prior to the Games.\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 940, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"South Africa's other five medals are one gold medal (Tatjana Smith - women's 100m breaststroke), two silvers (Smith - women's 200m breaststroke, men's 4x100m relay) and two bronzes (men's rugby sevens, Alan Hatherly - men's mountain bike cross country).\", \"from\": 942, \"to\": 1195, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 942, \"end\": 954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.496930476628876e-12, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 1144, \"end\": 1157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Hatherly\", \"score\": 0.9999924602050241, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alan Hatherly\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Hatherly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Hatherly\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, new Minister of Sport, Arts and Culture,Gayton McKenzie, said that a 'big surprise' awaits South Africa's medal winners at the\\u00a0Paris Olympics 2024.\", \"from\": 1197, \"to\": 1355, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1299, \"end\": 1311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.496930476628876e-12, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As reported byThe South African website, in a discussion withSABC Sport, McKenzie said he expected Team South Africa to return home with 'eight medals' from this year's Games.\", \"from\": 1357, \"to\": 1532, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Although he was adamant that it remain a 'surprise' until officially communicated, it appears clear that Team SA gold, silver and bronze medal winners will receive something in addition to the financial incentives announced previously by Sascoc.\", \"from\": 1534, \"to\": 1779, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1644, \"end\": 1646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.